<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix"></span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p1.1"></span>Canon LVIII.  (Greek lxii.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p2"></span>Of the remaining idols or temples
which should be done away by the Emperors.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p3.1"></span>Wherefore</span> the most religious
Emperors should be asked <span id="fr_457"></span>[458](#fn_457.md) that
they order the remaining idols to be taken entirely away throughout all
Africa; for in many maritime places and in divers possessions the
iniquity of this error still flourishes:  that they command them to be
taken away and their temples, (such as are no ornament, being set up in
fields or out of the way places) be ordered to be altogether destroyed.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p5"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p5.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p6"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p6.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon LVIII.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p7"></span>The remains of the idols should be
abolished altogether.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p8"></span>This is Canon ij. of the Synod of
Carthage of June 15 (16), <span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lix-p8.1"></span>a.d.</span> 401.

